cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper proposes an end-to-end deep-learning algorithm framework for accurately detecting the myocardial infarction (MI) area at the pixel level using cardiac magnetic resonance images. This involves heart localization, motion statistical analysis, and fully connected discriminate layers. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category, as it involves image analysis and segmentation. It also involves machine learning techniques, such as deep learning, which makes it likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of recurrent neural networks and optical flows for motion analysis makes it likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the use of medical images and analysis makes it likely to belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
